hifiberry-dspprofiles (1.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add length-based SHA-1 checksum (<metadata type="checksum_sha1">) to
    every shipped profile, alongside the existing signature-based MD5.
    Lets sigmatcpserver identify a running profile via either algorithm,
    making the match resilient to either kind of accidental corruption.
  * Add tools/enrich-checksums.py — flashes each profile to a live DSP,
    reads the length SHA-1 from the running program, and writes it back
    to the XML. Used to regenerate the new metadata when profiles change.

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Mon, 11 May 2026 11:00:00 +0000

